item.title: Syntax Reference
item.description: This is a railroad schematic of the currently supported VirtData recipe syntax. If this is your first time reading this guide, it is best to start at the top and read in order. Once you are familiar with the page, it can be used as a handy reference. Conventions In this documentation, CAPITALIZED := sections refer directly to a syntax type, for reference purposes. Other sections accompany the syntax diagrams, and are more explanatory in nature.
